Generated Narrative: ImplementationGuide example.fhir.ph.roadsafety

Language: en

PHRoadSafetyIG

The official URL for this implementation guide is: 

https://build.fhir.org/ig/UPM-NTHC/PH-RoadSafetyIG/ImplementationGuide/example.fhir.ph.roadsafety

FHIR IG for road safety and health information in the Philippines

name: PHRoadSafetyIG
title: DRAFT PH Road Safety Implementation Guide
publisher: UP Manila - National Institutes of Health - National Telehealth Center

contact.name: UP Manila - National Institutes of Health - National Telehealth Center

description: FHIR IG for road safety and health information in the Philippines

extension.valueMarkdown: Automatically added as a dependency - all IGs depend on HL7 Terminology
Automatically added as a dependency - all IGs depend on the HL7 Extension Pack

resource.name: Composition - Facility Report
resource.description: Composition for facility/ONEISS navigation, structured into coded sections derived from the Road Safety MDS (ED vitals, conditions, outcome, documents, tasks). Enables IG UIs to present a consistent outline.

resource.name: Composition - Run Report
resource.description: Composition for EMS Run Report navigation, structured into coded sections derived from the Road Safety MDS (triage, vitals, counts, post‑crash, documents, tasks). Enables IG UIs to present a consistent outline.

resource.name: Condition - ICD-10 External Cause
resource.description: ONEISS: ICD-10 external cause codes (V01–Y36 etc.).

resource.name: Condition - ICD-10 Nature of Injury
resource.description: ONEISS: ICD-10 nature of injury codes (S00–T98).

resource.name: Condition - Initial Impression
resource.description: ONEISS: Initial impression on patient condition.

resource.name: Condition - Problem / Chief Complaint
resource.description: MDS89: Problem (chief complaint as code/text).

resource.name: DocumentReference - Cause of Road Crash
resource.description: MDS115: Post-crash report reference (URL preferred).

resource.name: DocumentReference - ONEISS Facility Report
resource.description: DocumentReference profile for the ONEISS facility report (scan or link).

resource.name: DocumentReference - ONEISS Run Form
resource.description: Run Report scanned form or structured document (MDS5/MDS4 workflow docs).

resource.name: DocumentReference - Party at Fault
resource.description: MDS221: Party-at-fault narrative/report.

resource.name: DocumentReference - Road Network Shape Files
resource.description: MDS225: Geospatial resources references.

resource.name: DocumentReference - Traffic Incident Management
resource.description: MDS224: Incident management logs/evidence.

resource.name: DocumentReference - Vehicle Condition
resource.description: MDS226: Vehicle condition documents; alternative structured observations may exist.

resource.name: Encounter - Facility
resource.description: Encounter profile for facility visits (ONEISS). Contains hospital identifiers and hospitalization.dischargeDisposition.

resource.name: Encounter - Transport / Run Report
resource.description: Encounter for EMS transport/run-report. Incorporates MDS: Incident number (req), Type/class, Received-by participant role.

resource.name: Facility Bundle (prescribed)
resource.description: Bundle profile that prescribes the required slices/resources for facility (ONEISS) submissions.

resource.name: Location - Incident / Scene
resource.description: Location profile for crash/incident scene with optional geocoordinates and free-text reference to road network shapefiles or external resources.

resource.name: MDS AVPU Level of Consciousness
resource.description: AVPU scale coded in SNOMED CT.

resource.name: MDS Breath Sounds
resource.description: Breath sounds by auscultation.

resource.name: MDS Condition of Patient
resource.description: Overall condition assertion (Alive/Dead).

resource.name: MDS Cyanosis
resource.description: Cyanosis presence/type.

resource.name: MDS Drowning Body of Water
resource.description: Type/body of water involved in drowning.

resource.name: MDS GCS Eyes
resource.description: GCS Eye opening (LOINC answers).

resource.name: MDS GCS Motor
resource.description: GCS Motor response (LOINC answers).

resource.name: MDS GCS Verbal
resource.description: GCS Verbal response (LOINC answers).

resource.name: MDS Injury Intent
resource.description: Intent of injury.

resource.name: MDS Injury Types
resource.description: Common injury morphology/types.

resource.name: MDS Logical Model to FHIR Mapping
resource.description: Maps elements from the MDSRoadSafety logical model to target FHIR R4 resources.

resource.name: MDS Mode of Transport to Facility
resource.description: Transport mode answer list (LOINC answers).

resource.name: MDS Outcome
resource.description: Outcome at discharge/release.

resource.name: MDS Pulse Quality
resource.description: Pulse quality (normal/thready/bounding).

resource.name: MDS Pulse Rhythm
resource.description: Pulse rhythm (regular/irregular).

resource.name: MDS Pupils
resource.description: Pupil findings.

resource.name: MDS Respiratory Rhythm
resource.description: Respiratory rhythm findings.

resource.name: MDS Status on Arrival
resource.description: Status upon reaching facility.

resource.name: MDSRoadSafety ValueSet
resource.description: Aggregated ValueSet of coded options from the MDS Road Safety dataset, prioritizing SNOMED CT first, then LOINC. One code per sheet row is retained based on this priority.

resource.name: Observation - Blood Pressure
resource.description: MDS76-77: Vital sign at scene (BP panel with systolic/diastolic).

resource.name: Observation - CCTV Available
resource.description: MDS227: CCTV video/reconstruction available.

resource.name: Observation - Collision Type
resource.description: MDS218: Collision type (Must Support).

resource.name: Observation - Condition of Patient
resource.description: MDS108: Alive/Dead or other condition upon assessment.

resource.name: Observation - Cyanosis
resource.description: MDS81: Cyanosis presence/type.

resource.name: Observation - Date Received
resource.description: MDS62: Date received; single anchor dateTime.

resource.name: Observation - ED Blood Pressure
resource.description: ONEISS: Vital sign at facility (BP panel).

resource.name: Observation - ED Heart Rate
resource.description: ONEISS: Vital sign at facility (HR).

resource.name: Observation - Extent of Injury
resource.description: MDS109: Extent/severity estimate/category (free text/category).

resource.name: Observation - External Cause (Generic)
resource.description: Generic pattern for boolean flag with optional coded specifics for external causes (bites, burns, drowning, etc.).

resource.name: Observation - Facility / ONEISS
resource.description: Observation profile for facility-collected vitals and clinical observations for ONEISS reporting. Intended to be derived from PH‑CORE Observation profile when available.

resource.name: Observation - Glasgow Coma Scale
resource.description: MDS83-86: GCS modeled as components (eyes, verbal, motor) with optional total integer.

resource.name: Observation - Heart Rate
resource.description: MDS73: Vital sign at scene (HR).

resource.name: Observation - Level of Consciousness
resource.description: MDS79: LOC; bind to AVPU/GCS category where available.

resource.name: Observation - Mode of Transport to Facility
resource.description: MDS118/119: Mode of transport to hospital/facility with optional free-text.

resource.name: Observation - Outcome at Discharge
resource.description: ONEISS: Outcome/condition at discharge (MDS53/58).

resource.name: Observation - Patients Involved Count
resource.description: MDS157: How many patients involved (integer).

resource.name: Observation - Pupils
resource.description: MDS80: Pupils size/reactivity summary.

resource.name: Observation - Respiratory Rate
resource.description: MDS70: Respiratory rate with MS, optional rhythm/breath sounds captured elsewhere.

resource.name: Observation - Scene / Base
resource.description: Base for scene/transport observations in the Run Report derived from MDS. Provides common elements and Must Support flags where applicable.

resource.name: Observation - Status on Arrival
resource.description: MDS116/117: Status upon reaching facility (e.g., conscious/unconscious).

resource.name: Observation - Temperature
resource.description: MDS78: Temperature with MS; method/site optional in notes or components.

resource.name: Observation - Time Departed Scene
resource.description: MDS66: Depart scene timestamp.

resource.name: Observation - Time Enroute
resource.description: MDS64: Unit dispatched/enroute timestamp.

resource.name: Observation - Time Hospital Arrival
resource.description: MDS67: Arrival at hospital timestamp.

resource.name: Observation - Time On Scene
resource.description: MDS65: Arrival on scene timestamp.

resource.name: Observation - Time Received
resource.description: MDS63: Use single dateTime; stored as valueDateTime.

resource.name: Observation - Time Station Arrival
resource.description: MDS68: Station return/available timestamp.

resource.name: Observation - Transport/Vehicular Accident Flag
resource.description: MDS41: Required flag for RS reporting.

resource.name: Observation - Triage Category (Scene)
resource.description: MDS111: Priority to Scene (Triage).

resource.name: Observation - Vehicles Involved Count
resource.description: MDS156: How many vehicles involved (integer).

resource.name: Road Safety Condition
resource.description: Condition profile for coding diagnoses, ICD-10 nature of injury, and external cause mappings required by the Road Safety MDS.

resource.name: Road Safety Minimum Dataset (MDS) Logical Model
resource.description: Abstract, sectioned logical model for the PH Road Safety MDS covering incident, patient, encounter, clinical, vitals, injuries, evidence/documents, workflow, and finance. Elements mirror the CSV rows; mappings point to target FHIR elements for subsequent profiling.

resource.name: Road Safety Task
resource.description: Task profile for workflow events related to report submission, coordination with receiving facilities, and delays (executionPeriod, notes) in the Road Safety MDS.

resource.name: Run Report Bundle (prescribed)
resource.description: Bundle profile that prescribes required slices/resources for EMS run reports.

resource.name: Task - Delay Reporting
resource.description: MDS9-10: Sources of delays, Duration of delay.
